Cook and Others,<br><br>
You mentioned we had to draw from our past to plan for the future.  All that we are is threaded to the future.  We have shared experiences, supernatural  events, training, pain and purely horrifying experiences.<br><br>
What ties all this together.  We understand the wounds exist.  We apparently all have some baggage to carry.  Some are more effective in the control of their lives.<br><br>
More than once we haved touched on faith in a higher force.  Our faith, religion, or just strong personal beliefs effect our mental well being.  Could it be that there is some lack of personal confidence that all these powers are in agreement.  Could it be we fear we will not be forgiven for our deeds and exist in some sort of limbo waiting on the answers.<br><br>
Cook, you mention your faith has carried you.  I agree.  We must be carried sometimes on this trip and a beacon must be before us to show the way.  We need to trust.  We need closure.<br><br>
